<h1>What is link spam?</h1>                                                                                                                  

<p class="glossary-intro"><dfn>Link spam</dfn> refers to any links between pages that are for the sole purpose of increasing the pages fortunes in the search engine rankings for certain search terms.</p>
                                                                                                                  
<p><a href="https://www.theseoniverse.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/link-spam-example.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-804" src="https://www.theseoniverse.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/link-spam-example.jpg" alt="example of link spam in action" width="800" height="600" /></a></p>

<p>Link spam often comes from link farms and often includes the overuse of optimised <a href="https://www.theseoniverse.com/glossary/anchor-text">anchor text</a>Â using the <a href="https://www.theseoniverse.com/glossary/keywords">keyword</a> term or terms the page is intended to rank for. Link spam does not tend to offer the end user any value at all.</p>

